    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, that's a good start. can you go a bit deeper on the 'rule of law' part? some of my students feel like they get stuck when the opposition says that enforcement is actually inhumane or that laws can be secondary to human rights. how would a sophisticated debater frame the 'rule of law' argument to counter that without sounding like they're just ignoring humanitarian concerns?",
